<title>USA: Faulding anticonvulsant gets FDA approval.</title>
<headline>Faulding anticonvulsant gets FDA approval.</headline>
<dateline>ELIZABETH, N.J. 1996-11-01</dateline>
<text>
<p>Faulding Inc said on Friday that its Purepac Pharmaceuticals Co unit received U.S. Food and Drug Administration approval to market clonazepam tablets, a generic anticonvulsant drug used to treat seizures.  </p>
<p>Clonazepam was a generic equivalent of Roche Holding Ltd 's Konopin, Faulding said.</p>
<p>Faulding said total brand and generic revenues in 1995 were about $260 million and the product was expected to be available for shipment to customers in the first quarter 1997.</p>
<p>The drug was used alone or as an adjunct in the treatment of the Lennox-Gastaut Syndrome akinetic and myoclonic seizures, Faulding said.</p>
<p>-- New York newsdesk 212-859-1610</p>
